{"id": "1481968778647437453", "channel_id": "1481968778647437453", "type": 0, "author_id": "396365366298935307", "author_name": "chillercroc", "author_bot": false, "content": "Previously, Light said that aside from GTulu, there wouldn't be more than 2 males this year because the narrative plotline wouldn't allow for it. But how come the same narrative allows for two crossovers?\nThere are also characters who have no ties to the main plot who got released already since then, but at least some loose connections could be made with those. It just kinda sounds like an excuse to keep releasing waifus. Also, how come most of the girls released since Thais are just conventionally attractive waifus with little to no monstrous features at all? Morimens had stood out from the sea of other gachas by how unique and creative their designs were, but now it's just hot girl after hot girl after hot girl. Are there plans to change this any time soon?", "timestamp": "2026-03-13T10:54:50.478000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "Brown_think", "emoji_id": "1459080117308620996", "count": 6}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1481968778647437453", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Character ratios and design question", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1361169005435420785"]}
